we need multi cloud deployment using other deployment targets like aws lambda, ECS, EC2 in Azure functions, servers etc????


Got it â€” since your goal is multi-cloud deployments including AWS (Lambda, ECS, EC2), Azure Functions, VMs, and Kubernetes, this heavily favors Spinnaker over most GitOps-native tools like Argo CD or Tekton, because:

Argo CD / Flux / Tekton are Kubernetes-native, so they donâ€™t natively support AWS Lambda / EC2 / ECS / Azure Functions / traditional servers.

Spinnakerâ€™s Clouddriver handles multi-cloud deployments across AWS, Azure, GCP, Kubernetes, OpenStack, and even on-prem VMs.

Spinnaker supports blue/green, canary, rolling deployments across all these targets.

Hereâ€™s a detailed breakdown:

1. Deployment Targets Spinnaker Supports
Cloud / Target	Supported?	Notes
AWS EC2	âœ…	Classic EC2 instances, ASGs
AWS ECS	âœ…	Containerized workloads
AWS Lambda	âœ…	Serverless functions
Azure Functions	âœ…	Serverless functions
Azure VMs	âœ…	VM Scale Sets
GCP Compute	âœ…	VM / GKE clusters
Kubernetes	âœ…	Any cluster, multiple namespaces
OpenStack / VMware	âœ…	On-prem VMs
Cloud Foundry	âœ…	Application deployments

So if your organization uses multiple clouds + serverless + Kubernetes, Spinnaker is the only open-source tool that natively supports all of them in a unified pipeline.

2. How Multi-Cloud Works in Spinnaker

Clouddriver manages accounts for each cloud provider.

AWS: IAM roles / credentials

Azure: Service principal / credentials

GCP: Service account JSON

Pipeline stages can target different clouds in the same pipeline.

E.g., first stage: deploy Lambda

Next stage: deploy EC2 ASG

Next stage: deploy Kubernetes app

Canary / Blue-Green works across clouds.

Artifacts (Docker images, ZIP packages, config files) are stored in cloud object stores and are accessible to all targets.

3. Pipeline Example for Multi-Cloud
Pipeline: HolidayApp Deployment
--------------------------------
1. Find Artifact (Docker image or ZIP for Lambda)
2. Deploy to AWS Lambda (stage)
3. Deploy to AWS ECS (stage)
4. Deploy to Azure Functions (stage)
5. Deploy to Azure VM (stage)
6. Run canary analysis (optional)
7. Manual approval
8. Rollout complete


This can all be managed in one Spinnaker pipeline with one UI, unlike Tekton / Argo CD where youâ€™d need multiple clusters/repos.

4. Why Other Open-Source Tools Are Not Enough
Tool	Multi-cloud Support	Notes
Argo CD	âŒ	K8s-only
Argo Rollouts	âŒ	K8s-only
FluxCD	âŒ	K8s-only
Tekton	âŒ	K8s-only, can run serverless tasks but not deployment targets natively
Keptn	âš 	Focused on progressive delivery and SLO validation; needs upstream deploy tools

Conclusion: Only Spinnaker (OSS or Armory) meets the requirement out-of-the-box for multiple clouds + serverless + VMs + Kubernetes.

5. Enterprise Considerations

Fork Spinnaker internally (as we discussed) for compliance/security.

Internal Docker images for Clouddriver, Orca, Gate, etc.

Internal plugins for additional cloud integrations or policy enforcement.

Accounts setup for each cloud: AWS IAM roles, Azure service principals, GCP service accounts.

Artifact storage: S3 / GCS / internal registry accessible to all clouds.

âœ… Recommendation

Use Spinnaker OSS or Armory Enterprise.

Configure all your cloud accounts in Clouddriver.

Deploy pipelines across AWS, Azure, and K8s using one unified interface.

For serverless (Lambda / Azure Functions) and VM deployments, Spinnaker is currently the only open-source option that fully supports these targets in one pipeline.

